THOUGHT: The program only uses the status column to map to a set of allowed actions. Nulls are explicitly skipped (checked via pd.isna), so completeness is not required. The critical data quality requirement is that any non-null status value must be one of the allowed categories. Therefore, the appropriate pydeequ Check constraint is to ensure the status column values are contained within the allowed set. I will create constraints.json with this single constraint.

```bash
cat <<'EOF' > constraints.json
{
  "constraints": [
    ".isContainedIn('status', ['COMPLETED', 'CANCELLED', 'IN_PROGRESS', 'UNDER_REVIEW'])"
  ]
}
EOF
```
